<h2 p align="center">II</h2>
<h2 p align="center">The Bahmalow</h2>
<h3 p align="center">The Letter and the Spirit</h2>

<h2 p align="center">---</p>

In a dark and shining place, a creature made of ends of things rolled around in search of ingredients.

"Spicy sweet!", it chirped and hollered as it bounced up corners and flew through walls, all in search of the spicy sweet. It went to and fro wobbling and wiggling and giggling and smiggling.

<i>Boing Boing Boing</i>

Until at once it came at an impasse. It realized that there was no such thing as <i>ingredients</i> or spicy, or sweet. Bahmalow, or the woggling (as it was called by its enemies), would need to fathom them.

"Ingrediemts" [ sic ], it muttered to itself.

The woggling inflated into a new room, and continued inflating and rebounding about things for days and centuries. Then, one day, as it was reflating and conflating, it realized something else.

"There's no such thing as fathoming something..."

The woggling exploded and imploded across the galaxy slash universe in order to find out about what it's like to have an idea about something. So that it could make the stew, which contains, or is called, Spicy Sweet.

"Hmmm", The woggling considered. Thinking possibly, its difficulty lie in the structure of words and language, and it was possible that this etymological thought prison was preventing it from attaining its culinary goal.

"😔🙏 🍲" The woggling chirped, but still, nothing.

The woggling deflated and sputtered and whizzed about the world for centuries on seemingly without hope, and, starving. In the world of the Wogglings, there was no food. Because the woggling could not find food, or make food real, because it failed in its mission, the Woggling and all of it friends and family died.

<h2 p align="center">THE END</p>

<br class="page-break">

Or was it? The woggling reformed and resapiated ontologically into the realms of the real. In the empty void of nonexistence, where nothing exists, the place before birth and after death, of empty space, and void of thought or object, the woggling found no answers. Its constituent parts crunched together again into being.

"Ouch... my ribs."

"Nothing is true..." The woggling intellected. And suddenly... The woggling felt itself being pulled, converging across multiple bodies, on a snowy field somewhere. It opened "eyes" and found itself surrounded by jerking bags of chitin and blood, brass and iron.

